drawnet.lib.ddl
Class DMSErrors

java.lang.Object
  drawnet.lib.ddl.DMSErrors
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.lang.Cloneable
public class DMSErrors
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Cloneable

Manages error status.
Used in Formalism & Model to store the last error condition on operations (element and property operations are monitored in both structures).
Errors are available as static labels (e.g.: DMSErrors.OK).
Possible values:

  • OK
  • DUPLICATE_ID
  • ID_NOT_FOUND
  • WRONG_TYPE
  • VIOLATED_CONSTRAINT
  • NULL_POINTER

See Also:
Formalism.getErrorManager()
